<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397402>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 11. A–D. Reteporella ilala n. sp. A. Close-up of the orifice with beaded anter and suboral avicularium forming a pseudosinus (SAMC-A028986) (scale bar = 0.1 mm, magnified x200). B. Developing ooecium and different types of avicularia (SAMC-A029107) (scale bar = 0.2 mm, magnified x100). C. View of ovicelled zooid with ooecium covered by secondary calcification (SAMC-A029107) (scale bar = 0.2 mm, magnified x75). D. Close-up of ooecia covered by secondary calcification, except frontal fissure (SAMC-A029107) (scale bar = 0.1 mm, magnified x150). E–F. Triphyllozoon sp. (SAMC-A028905) E. View of trabeculae and autozooids (scale bar = 0.4 mm, magnified x35). F. Orifice and adventitious avicularia (scale bar = 0.2 mm, magnified x75)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4397402/files/figure.png" .

